.TH bessel 3
.SH NAME
.PP
\*Lbessel\*O, \*Lj0\*O, \*Lj1\*O, \*Ljn\*O, \*Ly0\*O, \*Ly1\*O, \*Lyn\*O \- Computes Bessel functions
.SH LIBRARY
.PP
\*OMath Library (\*Llibm.a\*O)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*L#include <math.h>
.PP
\*Ldouble j0  (\*Ldouble \*Vx\*L);
.nL
\*Lfloat  j0f (\*Lfloat  \*Vx\*L);
.nL
\*Ldouble j1  (\*Ldouble \*Vx\*L);
.nL
\*Lfloat  j1f (\*Lfloat  \*Vx\*L);
.nL
\*Ldouble jn  (int \*Vn\*L, \*Ldouble \*Vx\*L);
.nL
\*Lfloat  jnf (int \*Vn\*L, \*Lfloat  \*Vx\*L);
.nL
\*Ldouble y0  (\*Ldouble \*Vx\*L);
.nL
\*Lfloat  y0f (\*Lfloat  \*Vx\*L);
.nL
\*Ldouble y1  (\*Ldouble \*Vx\*L);
.nL
\*Lfloat  y1f (\*Lfloat  \*Vx\*L);
.nL
\*Ldouble yn  (\*Lint \*Vn\*L, double \*Vx\*L);
.nL
\*Lfloat  ynf (\*Lint \*Vn\*L, float  \*Vx\*L);\*O
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "bessel functions"
.iX "j0 function"
.iX "j1 function"
.iX "jn function"
.iX "y0 function"
.iX "y1 function"
.iX "yn function"
The \*Lj0(\|)\*O, \*Lj0f(\|)\*O, \*Lj1(\|)\*O,
and \*Lj1f(\|)\*O functions return the Bessel
function of \*Vx\*O of the first kind, of orders 0 (zero) and 1, respectively.
.PP
The \*Ljn(\|)\*O and \*Ljnf(\|)\*O functions return the Bessel function
of \*Vx\*O of the first kind of order \*Vn\*O.
.PP
The \*Ly0(\|)\*O, \*Ly0f(\|)\*O, \*Ly1(\|)\*O, and \*Ly1f(\|)\*O
functions return the
Bessel functions of \*Vx\*O of the second kind, of orders 0 (zero) and
1, respectively.
.PP
The \*Lyn(\|)\*O and \*Lynf(\|)\*O  functions return the Bessel function
of \*Vx\*O of the second kind of order \*Vn\*O.
.PP
Bessel functions are used to compute wave variables, primarily
in the field of communications.
.PP
.\".iS
